description:
&lt;p&gt;The opportunity has arisen for a Band 6 Specialist Paediatric&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Paediatric Physiotherapist (Experienced Rotational) to join the Paediatric Physiotherapy Service of Cwm Taf Morgannwg University Health Board on full time hours permanently.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The post holder will be responsible for managing a caseload independently and will have responsibility for delivering services within a special school. This post rotates across the 4 bases for Paediatric Physiotherapy which include Royal Glamorgan Hospital Children Centre, Ysbyty Cwm Cynon Children Centre, Princess Of Wales Hospital Children Centre and Carnegie Clinic.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The post holder will work closely, with hospital, community, education and local authority based Multi-disciplinary Teams in order to maintain continuity of service and to be responsible for the effective treatment and management of children and young people with special needs and complex physical difficulties in order to maximise potential and self-management.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The post holder will lead on the delivery of services to Children and Young People with a Primary Respiratory Pathology eg Cystic Fibrosis and Children and Young People with Neuromuscular Conditions.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The physiotherapy department will be looking for an HCPC registered physiotherapist who can demonstrate previous rotations to core areas and experience and exposure of working in paediatric Physiotherapy and have a good working knowledge of NHS systems and procedures.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The post holder will need to be a team player who enjoys working in a fast paced environment. You will need excellent clinical reasoning, time management, observation and communication skills and be able to demonstrate a genuine interest in achieving well being and positive health outcomes for the population we serve.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The post offers opportunities to enthusiastic and motivated staff to develop and share their skills. The service supports involvement in audit, practice supervision, in-service training, and continuing professional development with emphasis placed on regular supervision and support from experienced colleagues.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The post holder will require the ability to perform and cope with all aspects of manual handling and carry out the full range of duties required of the post.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The ability to speak Welsh is desirable for this post; Welsh and/or English speakers are equally welcome to apply.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Closing Date: 18/11/20&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For further details / informal visits contact:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;NameDonna MorrisJob titleProfessional Manager Paediatric PhysiotherapyEmail addressDonna.Morris@wales.nhs.ukTelephone number01443 715300&lt;/p&gt;
